# StandardModel.Bosons

Boson representation data.

The Standard Model gauge bosons are in the adjoint representations:
  Gluons   g  : 8 of SU(3)_c,  singlet of SU(2)_L,  Y = 0
  W bosons W  : singlet of SU(3)_c,  3 of SU(2)_L,  Y = 0
  B boson  B  : singlet of SU(3)_c,  singlet of SU(2)_L, Y = 0

The Higgs boson is a scalar:
  H : (1, 2, +1)  — complex doublet

After electroweak symmetry breaking SU(2)_L × U(1)_Y → U(1)_em, the physical
bosons are: photon γ, W±, Z⁰, and 8 gluons.

Status: stub.
